/*!

\page airinv-config
	Configuration Script for the C++ Simulated Airline Inventory Management System Library

\section sec_synopsis SYNOPSIS
<b>airinv-config</b> <tt>[--prefix] [--version] [--libs] [--cflags]</tt>

\section sec_description DESCRIPTION

\e airinv-config is a tool that is used by configure to determine the
compiler and linker flags that should be used to compile and link
programs that use \e AirInv. It is also used internally by the .m4
macros, that are included with \e AirInv, for GNU autoconf.

\section sec_options OPTIONS

\e airinv-config accepts the following options:

 \b --help<br>
    Display this help and exit

 \b --prefix<br>
    Show the AirInv installation prefix.

 \b --version<br>
    Print the currently installed version of AirInv on the standard output.

 \b --libs<br>
    Print the linker flags that are necessary to link with the AirInv library.

 \b --cflags<br>
    Print the compiler flags that are necessary to compile with the
    AirInv library.

 \b --sampledir<br>
    Show where the (StdAir CSV) sample files are located.

 \b --mandir<br>
    Show where the manual pages are located.

 \b --infodir<br>
    Show where the information pages are located.

 \b --docdir<br>
    Show the documentation base directory.

 \b --htmldocpath<br>
    Show where the HTML documentation is located.

 \b --refmanpath<br>
    Show where the PDF documentation is located.

\section sec_see_also SEE ALSO
\b airinv(1), \b airinv_parseInventory(1), \b AirInvServer(1), \b AirInvClient(1), \b airinv-library(3)

